Gg_CarPark

Made by The Giblets of Jesus

___________________________________ This map originally started out as a scenery test about 9 months ago after seeing something which caught my eye while I was traveling around Bournemouth (South-West England), a small car park with some foliage centered in the middle of it, with trees poking through the second level, and example of how people and architecture can adapt around nature, even inside a heavily urbanized area. Tl;Dr I saw some cool shit in a car park and made it into a test map :P Anyway, I dug this up recently and decided to make something of it by transforming it into a GunGame map. Gameplay is centered around the map's isometric, "figure of 8" design and features a good blend of long and medium ranged combat. ___________________________________

A few Features of this map:

+Constant, high FPS +HDR +90 Spawns (you can never have too many :P) +Volumetric lighting in spawn points +Isometric, "Figure of 8 design" design. ___________________________________

Like this map? Try the Gg_CarPark Menu Background :D

Gg_cabinwars is my first attempt at a map. I originally did it to give something back to my clan, and it turned out to be a very meditative experience. This map took the better part of three weeks to complete, but I've learned a lot in that short time (figuring out how to embed images into the bsp took a while hehe). I tried to focus on dynamics. That is, a fair amount of cover while retaining multiple access points across the map. Maybe I just read too far into it. Either way, here it is.

READ ME - gg_bunker_arena_jon

----------------------------------------------------

BUNKER ARENA
BY JON

----------------------------------------------------

DESCRITPTION:
A small sized gungame map featuring two bunkers inside an enclosed area and an underground
building connecting the two.  Both teams start inside their bunkers and can either fight
aboveground or underground.  Each path leads to the opposing team's bunker and each path
features plenty of objects to hide behind.

----------------------------------------------------

INSTALLATION:
Simply place both the .bsp and .nav files into your map folder.  Your map folder is located
here: C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\(your account name)\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

----------------------------------------------------
